      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "WALLACE, Idaho, June IA\nThree ministers have gone fishing.\nThey are Rev. r. +. Carter of the\nCongregations church, Rev. P. w.\nWood of the Holy Trinity and Rev.\nG. w. Williams of the Methodist.\n\n\nREPUBLIC. Wash, June IA\nHarry Surrel, Jr.. II, fell from a\n25-foot bank and broke his neck.\nHe died instantly. The accident\nhappened in view of the miners.\n\n\nTRINIDAD, Wash, June IA\nGreat Northern engines Nos. 1927\nand 1928 met in head-on collision\nin the mountains here yesterday,\none engineer jumped, received\nminor injuries."
